a:3:{s:6:"page_1";s:653:"<p>From full-page video backgrounds and sliders to galleries, buttons and widgets, Upfront does it all with <strong>regions and elements.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Regions</strong> are the backgrounds you can add to every page of your site to create headers, footers, and sections for your content.</p>
<p><strong>Elements</strong> are blocks of text, images, buttons, menus, galleries, contact forms, maps, custom code and more, which you'll find out more about in-depth further into this tutorial.</p>
<p>In this tutorial, we'll explore what regions and elements are all about and how to use them in the Upfront editor.</p>
<p>Let's get started.</p>
