a:3:{s:6:"page_1";s:968:"<p>While Upfront provides a huge range of elements that look great on any site out-of-the-box, there will be times when you want to take your customizations a step further. That’s where presets and custom CSS come in.</p>
<p>Say, for example, you want all of the CTA buttons on your site to look exactly the same, right down to the typeface, colors, size and border style. Creating a preset allows you to capture all of this style information, which you can then apply to other CTAs uniformly without having to style each and every button.</p>
<p>Then there’s custom CSS and the ability to add your own code, which is undoubtedly one of Upfront’s most powerful features. You can edit CSS for everything across your site, including regions and elements.</p>
<p>In this tutorial, I’ll show you how to create and edit presets, and also walk you through some practical examples of how to use custom CSS to add some pizazz to your site.</p>
<p>Let’s dive in!</p>
